      <rules>
        <rule name="Blade Parry" id="ca74-bd70-558a-7775" hidden="false">
          <description>The Weapon Skill Characteristic of a Model with this Special Rule is considered to be one point higher than normal when determining the score an opposing Model needs to Hit this Model in the Strike Step of the Challenge Sub-Phase or the Make Hit Tests Step of the Resolving an Initiative Step Step (this does not modify the Weapon Skill Characteristic of the Model in this Unit for the purposes of Hit Tests made for their own attacks).</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Hive Lord" id="06eb-8c44-6702-af41" hidden="false">
          <description>If the Mission being played has a Deploy Armies Step, at the end of this step, the Controlling Player of a Model with this Special Rule can deploy up to three Units again. When they do so, any of those Units can leave any Unit they have joined before being Deployed and can join a different Unit by being Deployed within Unit Coherency of it, if it is possible for those redeployed Units to join other Units. This Special Rule cannot be used to deploy any Units on the Battlefield outside of the Controlling Player’s Deployment Zone, or to deploy any Units that are Embarked upon a Model with the Transport Sub-Type.


In addition, while a Model with the Hive Lord Special Rule is on the Battlefield, the result of Reserves Tests made by the Controlling Player are automatically passed. And Models within Synapse Range of a Model with the Hive Lord Special Rule add a modifier of +1 to the value of X in any variant of the Line (X) Special Rule they have.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Synapse Horror" id="5f6e-d1b3-a3c3-deb4" hidden="false">
          <description>A Model with this Special Rule has multiple Psychic Disciplines</description>
        </rule>
      </rules>
