      </categoryLinks>
      <rules>
        <rule name="Brood Mother" id="b682-710a-1f3e-d591" hidden="false">
          <description>A model with this ability treats Termagants as if they had the Bitter Duty ability.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Brood Progenitor" id="004e-cca4-0d46-0c18" hidden="false">
          <description>In the Controlling Player’s Movement Phase as the Active Player, when a Model with the Brood Progenitor Special Rule has been selected, but either before or after it has been moved, the Controlling Player of that Model may activate this Special Rule. Once activated, the Controlling Player may add a Termagant Brood consisting of 10 Models to their army and place the Unit within 6” of the Model with the Brood Progenitor Special Rule and within Unit Coherency of all Models in the entering Unit. No Models may be placed within 1” of an enemy Model, any Battlefield Edge or a piece of Impassable Terrain. Any Models that cannot be placed using these Rules must be Removed as a Casualty immediately. Players can never score Victory points for the destruction of the Termagant Brood Unit added via this Special Rule and they do not count as Units for the Last Man Standing Special Rule</description>
        </rule>
      </rules>
    </selectionEntry>
