  <catalogueLinks>
    <catalogueLink type="catalogue" name="Special Rules" id="3de1-6143-a5d2-4db0" targetId="a2f9-617e-a8d9-a2a6"/>
  </catalogueLinks>
  <sharedRules>
    <rule name="Synapse Creature (X)" id="414d-fed2-22f0-3874" hidden="false">
      <description>Models within Synapse range have better Leadership, Cool, are immune to Characteristic Check modifiers, and can remove Tactical Statuses in the Start Phase.


Models with this Special Rule have a Synapse range of X”. Friendly Units with the Tyranid Trait gain all of the following benefits while at least one Model is within Synapse range. Models with the Synapse Creature (X) Special Rule also gain the following benefits:
• Models within Synapse range may use the Leadership and Cool Characteristics of the Synapse source for any Leadership or Cool Checks.
• Models within Synapse range or with the Synapse Creature (X) Special Rule never suffer negative modifiers when making Leadership Checks or Cool Checks.
• During the Effects Sub-Phase in the Start Phase of Controlling Player’s Turn, the Controlling Player may make a Check to remove a single Tactical Status from any number of Units within Synapse range. Each unit may only attempt this Check once per Turn.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Weapon Beast" id="8ab5-0af0-af0a-fb0e" hidden="false">
      <description>A Model with this Special Rule gains a bonus of +1 to its Attacks Characteristic as long as the Model is equipped with more than one Melee Weapon.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Symbiotic Targeting" id="ddc2-81fa-8a0b-751b" hidden="false">
      <description>When a Model with this Special rule is making a Shooting Attack, a modifier of +1 is added to the Model’s Ballistic Skill Characteristic if the Model with this Special Rule remained Stationary in the Controlling Player’s previous Movement Phase</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Shadow in the Warp (X)" id="3770-65f8-22dc-8b85" hidden="false">
      <description>Enemy Models with the Psyker Trait within X” of a Model with the Shadow in the Warp (X) Special Rule roll an additional Dice and discard the lower roll when making Willpower Checks.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Swarm Leader" id="1ffc-3ce3-b258-6b90" hidden="false"/>
    <rule name="Instinctive Behavior (Lurk)" id="62df-4991-d3d6-ee1d" hidden="false">
      <description>This Special Rule is always followed, in brackets, by either Lurk or Feed, which corresponds to a two below. During the Effects Sub-Phase in the Start Phase of your Turn, all Tyranids Units with this Special Rule that are outside of the Synapse range of any friendly Synapse Creatures must take a Leadership Test unless they are engaged in combat or have a Tactical Status. If the Test is passed, the Unit acts normally during this turn. If the Test is failed, then Unit must act in accordance with the following:

- Lurk: The Unit may not move in the Movement Phase and may not declare any charges. The unit must attempt a Shooting Attack if there is an Enemy unit within range, and must target the closest enemy unit possible that is within its line of sight and is a valid target for a Shooting Attack. If two or more targets are equally close then the Controlling Player chooses which will be the target of a Shooting Attack.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Instinctive Behavior (Feed)" id="af6e-fee8-0e26-77d9" hidden="false">
      <description>This Special Rule is always followed, in brackets, by either Lurk or Feed, which corresponds to a two below. During the Effects Sub-Phase in the Start Phase of your Turn, all Tyranids Units with this Special Rule that are outside of the Synapse range of any friendly Synapse Creatures must take a Leadership Test unless they are engaged in combat or have a Tactical Status. If the Test is passed, the Unit acts normally during this turn. If the Test is failed, then Unit must act in accordance with the following:

- Feed: The unit may not make any Shooting Attacks. During the Movement Phase, the Unit must move towards any enemy units, moving as much of their movement as possible. And the unit must attempt a Charge if there is an Enemy Unit within range, and must target the closest Enemy Unit possible that is within its line of sight and is a valid target for a Charge. If two or more targets are equally close then the Controlling Player chooses which will be the target of the Charge</description>
    </rule>
  </sharedRules>
  <categoryEntries>
    <categoryEntry name="Monster Model Type" id="b1e4-8128-1b2c-4d12" hidden="false"/>
    <categoryEntry name="Swarm Leader" id="b91d-4085-6c33-18b0" hidden="false">
      <rules>
        <rule name="Swarm Leader" id="cc03-55f5-b335-e8ac" hidden="false">
          <description>If an Army’s Primary Detachment is from the Tyranid Army List, the Controlling Player gains one additional Reaction Point if that Detachment or a Warlord Detachment from the same Army List includes any Models with the Swarm Leader Trait.</description>
        </rule>
      </rules>
    </categoryEntry>
  </categoryEntries>
